-- Ghana Says Cocoa Purchases Estimated at 400,000 Metric Tons by Nov. 25
-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 2010-12-08T10:38:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-08/ghana-says-cocoa-purchases-estimated-at-400-000-metric-tons-by-nov-25.html
Ghana’s purchases of cocoa from
growers in the West African nation are estimated at about
400,000 metric tons in the week to Nov. 25, Tony Fofie, chief
executive officer of the Ghana Cocoa Board, said in a phone
interview today from Accra, the capital.  Ghana is the world’s second-biggest producer of cocoa,
after Ivory Coast.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
 mdzawu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  